      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TO THE NINES (1) scored at Mildura last month and hasn't been far from the placegetters in two subsequent runs, the latest when fourth at this venue. Has the benefit of the inside draw so can give this a mighty shake. KING SAINT (2) made it two wins on the trot last start when he got the cash by a head at Melton. This looks stronger but he led from wider in both of those wins so draws to be prominent. LAMBRO MACH (3) didn't do a bad job when fifth from a wider barrier last time and was beaten just over a metre when runner-up at Melton prior. FRUGAL FARE (9) may need some luck from the back row but has a fine record at this circuit and distance with two wins and placing from three attempts.",
